Aha! receives webhooks from hundreds of JIRA instances. Many of these webhooks were setup during expired product trials and so are no longer needed. The webhooks cause unnecessary load for Aha! since we filter them out, but probably much more load for the Atlassian cloud to generate.

It would be nice if webhooks could be disabled remotely by the receiver if they are no longer appropriate. e.g. by returning a 410 HTTP status code. If the receiver of the webhook POST returns a 410 code that would indicate that the endpoint no longer wanted to receive that webhook (e.g. because the account is closed).

By disabling the webhook, rather than deleting it, the user could more easily enable it in the future if they want to.

